'''Ari''' ([[Book of Numbers|Numbers]] 24:9) or '''Aryeh''' ([[2 Samuel]] 17:10) is the [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] for "[[lion]]", cognate to [[Akkadian language|Akkadian]] ''aria'', [[Aramaic language|Aramaic]] ''arya''. The word is in use as a male first name. ''Ari'' was also used as a honorific for an important man.

''Gur-aryeh'' "lion cub" is attested in [[Jacob]]'s blessing on [[Judah]] ([[Genesis]] 49:9), "Judah is a lion's whelp; on prey, my son, have you grown".

The name [[Ariel|Ari-el]] translates to "lion of [[El (god)|God]]".

